DataElement.preferredDefinition: A pre-clinical or clinical study in human beings in which individuals are assigned by an investigator based on a protocol to receive specific interventions. The individuals are then followed and biomedical and/or health outcomes are assessed.:A detailed examination, analysis, or critical inspection of a subject designed to discover facts about it.:A rule which guides how an activity should be performed.:An organized collection of records that describe a particular body of data._Occurring first in time or sequence; original; of greatest rank or importance or value.:To possess every necessary or normal part or component or step; having come or been brought to a conclusion.:The particular day, month and year an event has happened or will happen.:Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.:A symbol or combination of symbols which is given an arbitrary meaning within a systematized collection of concepts used for data representation._The code that indicates whether the primary completion date is actual or anticipated.

A detailed examination, analysis, or critical inspection of a subject designed to discover facts about it.
